commit.message:
Fix simple typo: overidden -> overridden (#195)

Closes #194

Fix tests (#183)

The main goal of this commit is to fix
the test_encoding_from_filelike test for Python 3.6+.

As well, it fixes a couple of warnings.

configobj.rst: Markup fix (#182)

Use code block instead of accidental block quote

Fix grammatical error in documentation (close #170) (#175)

* fixed #170

* fixed some typos

Use tuple for startswith when parsing comments

Saves a generator comprehension and any() call.

Delete the _a_to_u() helper method

Well meaning attempt at encoding correctness, but does
literal nothing. On Python 3, ascii values are already
decoded, on Python 2 ascii will get safely coerced to
unicode.

Remove fallback for bool() not existing

Project only supports Pythons new enough to have the
bool() builtin these days.

Simplify automated py3 changes for dict iteration

No functionality change, just simplifies some expressions
from automated Python 3 compatibility changes, where
creating extra lists and similar is not actually needed.
Allow other path-like objects as configspec
Fix DeprecationWarning in pytest
Fix DeprecationWarning in Python 3.7
Add support for Python 3.7
Upgrade Python syntax with pyupgrade https://github.com/asottile/pyupgrade
Drop support for EOL Python 2.6 and 3.3

Remove broken downloads badge (#172)

See https://github.com/badges/shields/issues/716.
docs: fix get_extra_values example (#166)
added .editorconfig (closes #133)
docs: run tests only for 2.7 and 3.4
docs: more compact 'supported versions' list
quoting: make helper an actual function, and use repr in exceptions

Roundtrip configs with triple quotes and newlines

Reported long ago as bzr bug lp:710410 but the fix never
made it to the 5.x configobj series.

It is possible to create a config which configobj cannot
read back, due to reversed logic in triple quote handling.

Adapted the bzr unit test by bialix and fixed the
behaviour.

Move some dottedQuadToNum doctests to pytest

Currently the dottedQuadToNum doctest can fail on Python 2
depending on sys.maxint of the platform.

Really doctests are not suitable for full coverage, so the
boundary case and spacing behaviour checking is better
in the pytest framework with doctests reserved for showing
what the fuction actually does.
typo
update autoenv script from master (closes #126)
more compact test
adding 'mock' to test deps

Always return unicode when encoding is given (closes #18)

As reported in github issue #18 when a file-like object is
given and the encoding param is passed configobj fails to
decode the data on Python 2. This is a regression from
the 4.7 releases.

Fix is simply to check first for binary types in _decode()
helper as six.string_types includes the bytes str type
on Python 2.

Support python 3.5 and 3.6 (#137)

* Support + test python 3.5 and 3.6
* Faster Travis builds

Support python 3.5 and 3.6, and run tests for those versions. Also run
tests for python 2.6, which was missing.

* Don't require sudo on travis

This basically makes tests start faster, and we're not using sudo anyway.

Trivial change to documentation. (#120)

Added section about correct & easy error reporting from parsing exceptions.
fix rewriting of CfgObjs with alternate comment markers
